s = datetime(2017, 10, 1)
e = datetime(2020, 8, 1)

delta = 12 * (s.year - e.year) + (s.month - e.month)
delta = delta*-1
In [3]:
def variance(data):
    # Number of observations
    n = len(data)
    # Mean of the data
    mean = sum(data) / n
    # Square deviations
    deviations = [(x - mean) ** 2 for x in data]
    # Variance
    variance = sum(deviations) / n
    return variance
In [4]:
def data(names):
    
    #yahoo download
    data = web.DataReader(names, 'yahoo', start=s, end=e)['Adj Close']
    
    for name in names:
        data['%'+name] = data[name].pct_change()
        data['v'+name] = data[name]
        #data['v2'+name] = data[name]
    data = data.drop(data.index[0])
    print(data)
    data2 = pd.DataFrame(columns = data.columns)
    
    for i in range(delta):
        for name in names:
            data2.loc[i,name] = data.loc[s+ relativedelta(months=i),name]
            data2.loc[i,'%'+name] = data.loc[s+ relativedelta(months=i),'%'+name]
            
            #data2.loc[i,'v'+name] = variance(list(data.loc[s+ relativedelta(months=i-1):s+ relativedelta(months=i+1),name]))
            data2.loc[i,'v'+name] = stat.variance(list(data.loc[s+ relativedelta(months=i):s+ relativedelta(months=i+1),'%'+name]))
        
    data2['date'] = [(s+relativedelta(months=i)).date() for i in range(delta)]

    for name in names:
        data2['n '+name] = np.nan

    data2['total'] = np.nan
    data2['check'] = np.nan
    
    #data2.drop(0,inplace = True)
    data2 = data2.reset_index(drop = True)

    return data,data2

# Heatmap
def heatmap(data,names):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20,20))     
    corr = data[names].corr(method='pearson')
    mask = np.zeros_like(corr)
    mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True

    with sns.plotting_context("notebook",font_scale=1.3):
        plot =sns.heatmap(corr,fmt = '.2f',annot=True,ax=ax,mask=mask,vmin=-1, vmax=1).set_title('Key Correlations between cryptocurrencies:')
        plt.show()
        plt.clf()

#Control method modelling
def control(data,names):
    total = 100000
    cache = 0
    cache2 = 0

    for i in range(delta):
        for name in names:

            budget = total/len(names)
            price = data.loc[i,name]
            quantity = budget/price

            data.loc[i,'n '+name] = quantity
            cache += quantity*price

        data.loc[i,'check'] = cache 
        cache = 0

        if i != delta-1:
            for name in names:
                newprice = data.loc[i+1,name]
                quantity = data.loc[i,'n '+name]
                cache2 += quantity*newprice


            data.loc[i,'total'] = cache2
            total = cache2
            cache2 = 0
    return data

def vis(data,names):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,7))     
    plot = sns.lineplot(x='date', y="check", data=data,ax=ax).set_title('Invested Sum along time:')
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Total sum')
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()
    
    data['%check'] = data['check'].pct_change() * 100
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,7))     
    plot = sns.barplot(x='date', y="%check", data=data,ax=ax).set_title('Pct change of Invested sum along time:')
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Pct change of Invested sum (%)')
    fig.autofmt_xdate()
    plt.show()
    plt.clf()

    data['%check2'] = data['%check'].abs()
    print()
    print('Avg pct change =',round(data['%check2'][1:].mean(),4),'%')
    print('volatility = ',round(stat.variance(list(data['%check'])[1:])**0.5,4),'%')

# Modelling method for variance
def variance(data,names):

    total = 100000
    cache = 0
    cache2 = 0
    
    weights = pd.DataFrame(index = data.index, columns = names)

    for i in range(delta):
        variances = [1/(data.loc[i,'v'+name]) for name in names]
        for name in names:

            vname = 1/(data.loc[i,'v'+name])

            weight = vname/sum(variances)
            
            weights.loc[i,name] = weight

            budget = total*weight

            price = data.loc[i,name]

            quantity = budget/price

            data.loc[i,'n '+name] = quantity
            cache += quantity*price

        data.loc[i,'check'] = cache 
        cache = 0

        if i != delta-1:
            for name in names:
                newprice = data.loc[i+1,name]
                quantity = data.loc[i,'n '+name]
                cache2 += quantity*newprice


            data.loc[i,'total'] = cache2
            total = cache2
            cache2 = 0

    return data,weights

def cmatrix(data,names):
    data = data[names]

    cdata =  pd.DataFrame(columns = names)
    dummy = pd.Series([1 for i in names])
    dummy = np.matrix([dummy])
    for i in range(delta):
        correlation = data.loc[s+ relativedelta(months=i):s+ relativedelta(months=i+1),:].corr()
        correlation = correlation.to_numpy()
        
        def inv2(x):
            return 1/x#.abs()
        correlation = pd.DataFrame(correlation).apply(inv2).to_numpy() #23.91,22.7 ;
        #correlation = np.linalg.inv(correlation)# 23.3

        matrix = np.matmul(dummy,correlation)
        matrix = matrix[0].tolist()    
        
        array1 = np.array(matrix[0])
        array1 = np.where(array1<0, 0, array1)
        matrix = array1.tolist()
        

        cdata.loc[len(cdata)] = matrix
    #print(cdata)
    return cdata

def matrix(data,cdata,names,str1):
    
    total = 100000
    cache = 0
    cache2 = 0

    for i in range(len(data)):
        dummy = [cdata.loc[i,str1+j] for j in names]
            
        for name in names:
            
            vname = (cdata.loc[i,str1+name])
            
            weight = vname/sum(dummy)
            
            
            
            budget = total*weight

            price = data.loc[i,name]

            quantity = budget/price

            data.loc[i,'n'+name] = quantity
            cache += quantity*price

        data.loc[i,'check'] = cache 
        cache = 0

        if i != delta-1:
            cache2 = 0
            for name in names:
                newprice = data.loc[i+1,name]
                quantity = data.loc[i,'n'+name]
                cache2 += quantity*newprice

            data.loc[i,'total'] = cache2
            total = cache2
            cache2 = 0
    return data

def cvmatrix(ldata,sdata,names):
    ldata = ldata[names]

    cdata =  pd.DataFrame(columns = names)
    dummy = pd.Series([1 for i in names])
    dummy = np.matrix([dummy])
    
    for i in range(delta):
        correlation = ldata.loc[s+ relativedelta(months=i):s+ relativedelta(months=i+1),:].corr()
        correlation = correlation.to_numpy()
        
        def inv2(x):
            return 1/x.abs()
        correlation = pd.DataFrame(correlation).apply(inv2).to_numpy()# NaN,22.36
        #pd.DataFrame(correlation).to_excel('cormatrix.xlsx')
        #correlation = np.linalg.inv(correlation)#30
        
        variance = pd.DataFrame(columns = names, index = names)
        for name in names:
           variance.loc[name,:] = [sdata['v'+name][i]**.5 for j in range(len(names))]
        
        variance = variance.to_numpy()
        varianceT = variance.T
        matrixv = np.multiply(variance,varianceT)
        #print(matrixv)
        #pd.DataFrame(matrixv).to_excel('varmatrix.xlsx')
        
        matrixcv = np.matmul(matrixv,correlation)
        
        matrix = np.matmul(dummy,matrixcv)
        matrix = matrix[0].tolist()    
        array1 = np.array(matrix[0])
        array1 = np.where(array1<0, 0, array1)
        matrix = array1.tolist()
        
        cdata.loc[len(cdata)] = matrix
    #print(cdata)
        
    return cdata

def metf(etf):#etf = series
    
    etfindex = list(etf.index)
    j = 0
    metf = []
    dates = []
    for i in range(delta):
    
        boo1 = True
        while boo1:
            
            if s+ relativedelta(months=i,days = j) in etfindex:

                metf.append(etf[s+ relativedelta(months=i,days = j)])
                
                j=0
                boo1 = False
                dates.append(s+ relativedelta(months=i,days = j))
            else:
                #print(s+ relativedelta(months=i,days = j))
                j += 1
        #print(i)
    
    return metf,dates

def etfmatrix(crypto,weight):
    
    wDIA = []

    for i in range(delta):
        
        sum1 = sum(crypto.loc[i,:])
        
        wDIA.append((sum1/(1-weight))-sum1)
    
    crypto2 = crypto.copy()
    crypto2['DIA'] = wDIA
    
    return crypto2
